setsw2:     set spectral width in 2nd evolution dimension (M)

	Syntex:		setsw2(nucleus,downfieldppm, upfieldppm):offset
	Description:	sw2 is set for the given spectral window and the
			nucleus and the appropriate offset is returned.
			Referencing also done.
        
	Example:	setsw2(tn,12,0)
			setsw2(dn2,130,80):dof2
			
	Related:	setsw
			setsw1     		
